            <div type="content">
                <div type="intro">
                <p>In this index is displayed a set of rules designed for SigiDoc in order to 
                    establish a scholarly edition of the seals' legend: the following thematic list contains 
                    all the mark-up necessary to visualise the Leiden symbols used in representing the 
                    editorial interventions on the legend's transcription (e.g. ( ), [ ], &lt; &gt;, ..., etc.). Among the different sets of conventions available through the EpiDoc 
                    stylesheet, SigiDoc is loosely based on those designed by <ref target="https://www.academia.edu/10020740/191_-_I_segni_diacritici_dieci_anni_dopo">Hans Krummrey 
                        and Silvio Panciera</ref>, with variations intended to make some of them more 
                    suitable for (Byzantine) sigillographic routines.</p>
            </div>
